Arguments.Name: BQ - Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba
CD - Congo, Democratic Republic of the
GB - United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland
GS - South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands
HM - Heard Island and McDonald Islands
SH - Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha
UM - United States Minor Outlying Islands
VC - Saint Vincent and the Grenadines
--account-sid
Arguments.Description: The SID of the Account requesting the AvailablePhoneNumber resources

Arguments.Name: --address-sid
Arguments.Description: The SID of the Address resource we should associate with the new phone number. Some regions require addresses to meet local regulations

Arguments.Name: --api-version
Arguments.Description: The API version to use for incoming calls made to the new phone number. The default is `2010-04-01`

Arguments.Name: --area-code
Arguments.Description: The area code of the phone numbers to read. Applies to only phone numbers in the US and Canada

Arguments.Name: --beta
Arguments.Description: Whether to read phone numbers that are new to the Twilio platform. Can be: `true` or `false` and the default is `true`

Arguments.Name: --no-beta
Arguments.Description: Whether to read phone numbers that are new to the Twilio platform. Can be: `true` or `false` and the default is `true`

Arguments.Name: --bundle-sid
Arguments.Description: The SID of the Bundle resource that you associate with the phone number. Some regions require a Bundle to meet local Regulations

Arguments.Name: --contains
Arguments.Description: The pattern on which to match phone numbers. Valid characters are `*`, `0-9`, `a-z`, and `A-Z`. The `*` character matches any single digit. For examples, see Example 2 and Example 3. If specified, this value must have at least two characters

Arguments.Name: --distance
Arguments.Description: The search radius, in miles, for a `near_` query.  Can be up to `500` and the default is `25`. Applies to only phone numbers in the US and Canada

Arguments.Name: --emergency-address-sid
Arguments.Description: The SID of the emergency address configuration to use for emergency calling from the new phone number

Arguments.Name: --emergency-status
Arguments.Description: The parameter displays if emergency calling is enabled for this number. Active numbers may place emergency calls by dialing valid emergency numbers for the country

Arguments.Name: --exclude-all-address-required
Arguments.Description: Whether to exclude phone numbers that require an Address. Can be: `true` or `false` and the default is `false`

Arguments.Name: --no-exclude-all-address-required
Arguments.Description: Whether to exclude phone numbers that require an Address. Can be: `true` or `false` and the default is `false`

Arguments.Name: --exclude-foreign-address-required
Arguments.Description: Whether to exclude phone numbers that require a foreign Address. Can be: `true` or `false` and the default is `false`

Arguments.Name: --no-exclude-foreign-address-required
Arguments.Description: Whether to exclude phone numbers that require a foreign Address. Can be: `true` or `false` and the default is `false`

Arguments.Name: --exclude-local-address-required
Arguments.Description: Whether to exclude phone numbers that require a local Address. Can be: `true` or `false` and the default is `false`

Arguments.Name: --no-exclude-local-address-required
Arguments.Description: Whether to exclude phone numbers that require a local Address. Can be: `true` or `false` and the default is `false`

Arguments.Name: --fax-enabled
Arguments.Description: Whether the phone numbers can receive faxes. Can be: `true` or `false`

Arguments.Name: --no-fax-enabled
Arguments.Description: Whether the phone numbers can receive faxes. Can be: `true` or `false`

Arguments.Name: --friendly-name
Arguments.Description: A descriptive string that you created to describe the new phone number. It can be up to 64 characters long. By default, this is a formatted version of the new phone number

Arguments.Name: --identity-sid
Arguments.Description: The SID of the Identity resource that we should associate with the new phone number. Some regions require an identity to meet local regulations

Arguments.Name: --in-lata
Arguments.Description: Limit results to a specific local access and transport area (LATA). Given a phone number, search within the same LATA as that number. Applies to only phone numbers in the US and Canada

Arguments.Name: --in-locality
Arguments.Description: Limit results to a particular locality or city. Given a phone number, search within the same Locality as that number

Arguments.Name: --in-postal-code
Arguments.Description: Limit results to a particular postal code. Given a phone number, search within the same postal code as that number. Applies to only phone numbers in the US and Canada

Arguments.Name: --in-rate-center
Arguments.Description: Limit results to a specific rate center, or given a phone number search within the same rate center as that number. Requires `in_lata` to be set as well. Applies to only phone numbers in the US and Canada

Arguments.Name: --in-region
Arguments.Description: Limit results to a particular region, state, or province. Given a phone number, search within the same region as that number. Applies to only phone numbers in the US and Canada

Arguments.Name: --limit
Arguments.Description: The maximum number of resources to return. Use '--no-limit' to disable

Arguments.Name: --mms-enabled
Arguments.Description: Whether the phone numbers can receive MMS messages. Can be: `true` or `false`

Arguments.Name: --no-mms-enabled
Arguments.Description: Whether the phone numbers can receive MMS messages. Can be: `true` or `false`

Arguments.Name: --near-lat-long
Arguments.Description: Given a latitude/longitude pair `lat,long` find geographically close numbers within `distance` miles. Applies to only phone numbers in the US and Canada

Arguments.Name: --near-number
Arguments.Description: Given a phone number, find a geographically close number within `distance` miles. Distance defaults to 25 miles. Applies to only phone numbers in the US and Canada

Arguments.Name: --no-header
Arguments.Description: Skip including of headers while listing the data

Arguments.Name: --page-size
Arguments.Description: How many resources to return in each list page. The default is 50, and the maximum is 1000

Arguments.Name: --properties
Arguments.Description: The properties you would like to display (JSON output always shows all properties)

Arguments.Name: --sms-application-sid
Arguments.Description: The SID of the application that should handle SMS messages sent to the new phone number. If an `sms_application_sid` is present, we ignore all of the `sms_*_url` urls and use those set on the application

Arguments.Name: --sms-enabled
Arguments.Description: Whether the phone numbers can receive text messages. Can be: `true` or `false`

Arguments.Name: --no-sms-enabled
Arguments.Description: Whether the phone numbers can receive text messages. Can be: `true` or `false`

Arguments.Name: --sms-fallback-method
Arguments.Description: The HTTP method that we should use to call `sms_fallback_url`. Can be: `GET` or `POST` and defaults to `POST`

Arguments.Name: --sms-fallback-url
Arguments.Description: The URL that we should call when an error occurs while requesting or executing the TwiML defined by `sms_url`

Arguments.Name: --sms-method
Arguments.Description: The HTTP method that we should use to call `sms_url`. Can be: `GET` or `POST` and defaults to `POST`

Arguments.Name: --sms-url
Arguments.Description: The URL we should call when the new phone number receives an incoming SMS message

Arguments.Name: --status-callback
Arguments.Description: The URL we should call using the `status_callback_method` to send status information to your application

Arguments.Name: --status-callback-method
Arguments.Description: The HTTP method we should use to call `status_callback`. Can be: `GET` or `POST` and defaults to `POST`

Arguments.Name: --trunk-sid
Arguments.Description: The SID of the Trunk we should use to handle calls to the new phone number. If a `trunk_sid` is present, we ignore all of the voice urls and voice applications and use only those set on the Trunk. Setting a `trunk_sid` will automatically delete your `voice_application_sid` and vice versa

Arguments.Name: --voice-application-sid
Arguments.Description: The SID of the application we should use to handle calls to the new phone number. If a `voice_application_sid` is present, we ignore all of the voice urls and use only those set on the application. Setting a `voice_application_sid` will automatically delete your `trunk_sid` and vice versa

Arguments.Name: --voice-caller-id-lookup
Arguments.Description: Whether to lookup the caller's name from the CNAM database and post it to your app. Can be: `true` or `false` and defaults to `false`

Arguments.Name: --no-voice-caller-id-lookup
Arguments.Description: Whether to lookup the caller's name from the CNAM database and post it to your app. Can be: `true` or `false` and defaults to `false`

Arguments.Name: --voice-enabled
Arguments.Description: Whether the phone numbers can receive calls. Can be: `true` or `false`

Arguments.Name: --no-voice-enabled
Arguments.Description: Whether the phone numbers can receive calls. Can be: `true` or `false`

Arguments.Name: --voice-fallback-method
Arguments.Description: The HTTP method that we should use to call `voice_fallback_url`. Can be: `GET` or `POST` and defaults to `POST`

Arguments.Name: --voice-fallback-url
Arguments.Description: The URL that we should call when an error occurs retrieving or executing the TwiML requested by `url`

Arguments.Name: --voice-method
Arguments.Description: The HTTP method that we should use to call `voice_url`. Can be: `GET` or `POST` and defaults to `POST`

Arguments.Name: --voice-receive-mode
Arguments.Description: The configuration parameter for the new phone number to receive incoming voice calls or faxes. Can be: `fax` or `voice` and defaults to `voice`

Arguments.Name: --voice-url
Arguments.Description: The URL that we should call to answer a call to the new phone number. The `voice_url` will not be called if a `voice_application_sid` or a `trunk_sid` is set
